{
  "text": "Where examined in detail, the excursion in terrestrial sections begins immediately above the K-Pg boundary clay in the fern spike interval, with the most negative values in the early phase of dicot recovery, and a return to preexcursion values no higher than 2-3 m up section (reviewed in [CITATION_1] . For our initial modeling we assume \u22122\u2030 (Text S2). If we instead assume an excursion of 0\u2030, comparable to the value at the top of the K-Pg boundary clay, or \u22123\u2030, the median CO 2 is 1,170 and 762 ppm, respectively. Neither of these changed estimates strongly affect our key interpretations.",
